body: This should be sorted now - let me know if you still have any issues with it

I am seeing this error in clang 3.7.0 with gcc 5.1.1. 

specifically /usr/include/wchar.h has 
#include <stddef.h> 
and it is somehow finding the one in /usr/lib/clang/3.7.0/include  (why?)

which uses __has_features(modules)

Is there a clang specific header I could include first, that would invoke the protections/fix ?

issue.title: phmap_config.h: error: missing binary operator before token "("
